this is a company called "Glabant". it was a devops role :                                                          Can you explain your experience with AWS services?

If we are going to implement a solution for microservices, how would you propose a solution to implement a microservices architecture?



Why do you prefer to start with EKS instead of ECS?

   
Follow-up: What are the capabilities of EKS that make it a better choice over ECS for this project?

How would you configure the Elastic Load Balancer to work against the EKS cluster?

How many public subnets and private subnets are you going to use in the VPC?

In which subnets are you going to locate the ECS cluster and the RDS instances?


How would you handle multiple environments (development, staging, production) using Terraform?


Can you explain the steps involved in creating a CICD pipeline for deploying a Spring Boot application to ECS?

Can you share your experience in handling a large number of servers and your administrative responsibilities?

    
Follow-up: What kind of administrative tasks and responsibilities have you had in managing a large number of servers?

Are you available to work online from Monday to Friday for the first six months and visit client offices twice a week?

