here are all the questions the interviewer asked during the discussion, including the follow-up questions:

Can you tell me about a time when you realized you needed a level of subject matter expertise to do your job well? What did you do about that?
What was the situation where you needed deeper expertise?
What did you do to acquire that deeper knowledge?
What was the result of gaining that expertise?

Can you give me an example of a complex problem that you solved with a simple solution?
What parts of the solution did you directly implement or change?
How did you know the solution addressed the problem? Were there any metrics or changes you observed?

What is the name of the physical address of a device on a network called?

Do you know what DNS stands for and what it does?
When you type in a website address in your browser, how does DNS resolve that in the background?

Can you name some standard directories in a Linux system?

How would you troubleshoot a full file system on a Linux server?
Can you provide some examples of standard directories in a Linux system?
How would you specifically troubleshoot a full file system? What commands would you use?

How would you monitor system performance and manage processes on a Linux server?
How would you monitor system performance and identify processes consuming high resources?

Do you have any questions about the role at Amazon?

